The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 4: In a relief to steel makers such as Essar, JSW and Ispat, state-run mining firm NMDC has decided to slash prices of its long-term iron ore by 25 per cent from December 1. NMDC had increased the iron ore rates by up to 40 per cent from April 1 this year. After the reduction, the rate of iron ore lumps used in steel making will drop to Rs 2,650 per tonne from Rs 3,710 per tonne.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 4: The Oberoi Group said its Trident Hotel in Mumbai would reopen from December 21, while the Oberoi would take at least four to six months before it could reopen. The Trident suffered far less damage compared with the Oberoi in the terror attacks last week.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 4: Punj Lloyd and US-based Thorium Power will form a joint venture by March 2009 to provide consultancy services for setting up and operating nuclear power plants in India, Southeast Asia and other regions.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 4: Tata Steels output grew 27 per cent in November. Hot metal production surged 5.78 lakh tonnes, a 26.8 per cent growth over the corresponding month last fiscal.                            
	 New York, Dec. 4: AT amp;T will slash 12,000 jobs while software maker Adobe will reduce its workforce by 600. Credit Suisse will cut 5,300 jobs, while Japans Nomura plans 1,000 job cuts at its London office in the wake of the financial crisis.                                                                                                                         
